messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
It's 515 East Rancho. I have people in my yard and the dogs in my yard from next door. I don't know what’s going on, but there's something happening here.
Okay, are you hearing yelling? What's going on?
Well, there are a bunch of them yelling about something. I don't know what. I'm going out to see what's going on.
Okay, don't approach them. Do not approach them. Go back in your house.
They're messing up my gardens.
You need to go back in your house. I'm going to get officers en route.
It's too late now. We've got one down.
Go back in your house. What did you say?
The guy that was in my yard started attacking me.
He jumped on me.
You need to go back in your house.
Well, you better... I'm in the house now. I got blood all over me.
Were you attacked by the dog?
No, the guy attacked me.
I'm advising the RP to go back in his house. He will not listen. Mike, what's your phone number?
Huh? What is your phone number?
Okay. Did you go back in your house?
I'm in the house.
The male subject attacked him. He is injured.
Who attacked you?
The guy next door.
Who is it?
I don't know who it is.
Where are you hurt?
His blood is all over. It's in my house. It's on my hands. It's on my guns.
Okay, why is his blood on you?
Well, because he was that close, that's why.
Okay, did you hit him? What happened?
He was attacking, but I shot him.
RP shot the male subject. I repeat, male subject has been shot. What kind of gun do you have?
It's a black.
Where is your gun?
It's in my house.
Is it next to you?
It's on my table. I'm having a problem. I got a heart thing, too. My heart's bugging me. I got to sit down.
Okay. Take a few deep breaths.
I can't understand you.
Mike, I want you to sit down and take a few deep breaths.
Yeah.
Where are you in the house?
I'm in my kitchen.
Okay. Take a few deep breaths trying to calm down.
I'm having some chest pains right now.
Okay. Is there any other injury?
I have to hang up. I need to get some other stuff here.
No, Mike, I need you to stay on the phone with me, okay?
I can't. I got to get some medication.
Mike? Mike.
